Client: BodyVision Medical Ltd



For patients with cancerous lung lesions, the average global survival rate is just 10%. 

In the US, where patients are privileged to have access to advanced imaging technologies & medical instruments made from composite materials used to launch satellites to the Moon and rockets to Mars - the survival rate is still just 18%!



The inability to reach the lesion leaves the patient with watchful waiting and its gloom cascade resulting in 90% mortality rates.



We develop all these modalities but theyre not improving the mortality rates. Recent studies on new robotic tools have concluded that these devices are just slight enhancements of existing modalities, with similar outcomes. 

The problem we were solving is not the real problem. 



What we are doing at Body Vision is simply connecting the dots. 

The variety of sensors doctors use are outputting a tremendous amount of information. We developed the LungVision platform to take all that data and pull it together into one intelligent mind. This allows for bronchial information to finally be fused, and presented in a complete way - making any lesion truly visible and accessible with standard biopsy tools. 



This level of clarity means doctors can actually reach the lesion easily, while watching it in real time. When you are looking at a 3D lesion through LungVision in real time - it's no different from actually looking through the patient. Finally, this question of localization accuracy is obsolete. 



Today, after 400 clinical procedures, the AI tissue detection performance of the 2nd Generation of LungVision is at 96% accuracy.

title.value: The future of lung cancer diagnostics and treatment
